Q1 -: What are the benefits of using CSS?
-> 1. Separation of Content and Style
   2. Consistency
   4. Responsive Design
   5. Animations 

Q2 -: What are the disadvantages of CSS?
-> 1. Browser Compatibility
   2. Learning Curve
   3. Lack of Security
   4. Limited Layout Control
   5. Performance Impact

Q3 -: What is the difference between CSS2 and CSS3?
-> CSS2 introduced a new box model which included padding, 
   borders, and margins. 
   CSS3 introduced the flexible box layout module, which allows
   for more flexible layouts.

Q4 -: Name a few CSS style components
->  (1)Selectors
    (2)Properties
    (3)Values
    (4)Box Model
    (5)Layout
    (6)Animations

Q5 -: What do you understand by CSS opacity? 
-> Opacity set a transparency of an element
   - You can give value between 0 to 1

Q6 -: How can the background color of an element be changed?
->  Ex-: h1{
            background-color : red;
         }

Q7 -: How can image repetition of the backup be controlled?
->   Ex-: h1 {
            background-repeat: no-repeat;
            }

Q8 -: What is the use of the background-position property?
->    Ex-: h1 {
            background-postion: center;
            /* center,top,right,left,bottom */
            }

Q9 -: Which property controls the image scroll in the background?
->    Ex-: h1 {
            background-attachment: fixed;
            }

Q10 -: Why should background and color be used as separate properties?
->      Background and color as separate properties in web     design and development  

Q11 -: How to center block elements using CSS1?
->    Ex-: h1{
            text-align: center;
            }

Q12 -: How to maintain the CSS specifications?
->    CSS specifications, you ensure that styling across your website or application remains consistent. This consistency enhances user experience and maintains the visual identity of your brand.

Q13 -: What are the ways to integrate CSS as a web page?
->    There are Three ways to integrate a CSS:
         (1)inline 
         (2)internal
         (3)External

      (1)inline tag:
            - Inline tag is use in a element
                Ex-: <p style="color: blue;> </p>

      (2)internal:
            - The <style> tag use in head section you can      use a CSS
               Ex-: <style>
                        h1 {
                           color: green;
                        }
                    </style>

      (3)External:
            -  you can connect with css file then you can use a CSS
               Ex-:  h1 {
                           color: green;
                        }

Q14 -:  What is embedded style sheets?
->  Embedded style sheets is also known as Internal style sheets
      - The <style> tag use in head section you can      use a CSS
         Ex -: <style>
                        h1 {
                           color: green;
                        }
               </style>

Q15 -: What are the external style sheets?
->   -  you can connect with css file then you can use a CSS
               Ex-:  h1 {
                           color: green;
                        }

Q16 -: What are the advantages and disadvantages of using external style sheets?
->    Advantages -:
                  (1) Consistency
                  (2) Ease of Maintenance
                  (3) Caching
                  (4) Separation of Concerns

      Disadvantages -:      
                  (1) HTTP Requests:
                  (2) Dependency
                  (3) Blocking Rendering
                  (4) Specificity and Inheritance Issues

Q17 -: What is the meaning of the CSS selector?
->    A CSS selector is a pattern used to select and style elements in an HTML document. It defines the elements to which a particular set of CSS rules will apply.

Q18 -: What are the media types allowed by CSS?
->    CSS supports several media types, which allow you to specify different styles for different types of devices or media.

Q19 -: What is the rule set?
->    In CSS, a rule set, also known simply as a rule, is a collection of one or more CSS declarations that define how an HTML element should be styled. Each rule set consists of a selector and a declaration block.
      Example -:
                  selector {
                     color:red;
                  }

Q20 -:  Create Layouts
->    Example -:
            Display top 10 IT companies list in html webpage

                  <!DOCTYPE html>
                  <html lang="en">
                  <head>
                     <meta charset="UTF-8">
                     <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
                     <title>TOP 10 IT COMPAINES</title> 
                     <style>
                        li {
                              margin-bottom: 25px;
                        }
                     </style>

                  </head>
                  <body>
                     <center>
                        <h1>TOP 10 IT COMPAINES</h1>
                     </center>
                     <ol>
                        <li>MICROSOFT</li>
                        <li>APPLE</li>
                        <li>GOOGLE</li>
                        <li>AMAZON WEB SERVICE</li>
                        <li>Oracle Corporation</li>
                        <li>Intel Corporation</li>
                        <li>Samsung Electronics </li>
                        <li>IBM (International Business Machines Corporation)</li>
                        <li>Cisco Systems </li>
                        <li>Tencent Holdings Limited</li>
                     </ol>
                     
                  </body>
                  </html>

